---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout title="Library" description="Deep dives into Eastern Christian topics — theology, history, practice — each one standalone.">

  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom:40px;">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Library</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title" style="font-size:34px;">Topics & Deep Dives</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        Every topic is self-contained. Start wherever your curiosity takes you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container" style="padding-bottom:80px;">

    <div class="library-filter-bar">
      <span class="filter-chip active">All</span>
      <span class="filter-chip">Theology</span>
      <span class="filter-chip">History</span>
      <span class="filter-chip">Practice</span>
      <span class="filter-chip">Spirituality</span>
      <span class="filter-chip">Ecumenism</span>
    </div>

    <div class="library-grid">
      <a href={`${base}/library/what-is-byzantine-catholic/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Identity</div>
        <h3>What Is a Byzantine Catholic?</h3>
        <p>Eastern tradition, Western communion — the Christians who hold both lungs together. Everything you need to know.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 15</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/theosis/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Theology</div>
        <h3>Theosis — Becoming God by Grace</h3>
        <p>The Eastern understanding of salvation isn't a courtroom verdict — it's a healing. Humanity was made to share in the divine nature.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 6</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/ecumenical-councils/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">History</div>
        <h3>The Seven Ecumenical Councils</h3>
        <p>From Nicaea to Nicaea II — the seven gatherings that defined what Christians believe and why icons matter.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 8</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/jesus-prayer/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Practice</div>
        <h3>The Jesus Prayer</h3>
        <p>"Lord Jesus Christ, Son of God, have mercy on me, a sinner." Eight words that contain an entire theology.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 10</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/ancestral-sin/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Theology</div>
        <h3>Ancestral Sin vs. Original Sin</h3>
        <p>Why Eastern Christianity doesn't teach inherited guilt — and what it teaches instead.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 5</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/great-schism/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Ecumenism</div>
        <h3>The Great Schism of 1054</h3>
        <p>What actually happened, what didn't, and why healing this wound matters more than scoring points.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 14</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/desert-fathers/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Spirituality</div>
        <h3>The Desert Fathers & Mothers</h3>
        <p>In the 4th century, thousands of Christians walked into the Egyptian desert. What they found there shaped all of Eastern spirituality.</p>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/iconostasis/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Practice</div>
        <h3>The Iconostasis Explained</h3>
        <p>The wall of icons that separates the nave from the sanctuary — every icon has a place, and every placement has a meaning.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 2</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/union-of-brest/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">History</div>
        <h3>The Union of Brest (1596)</h3>
        <p>How Eastern Christians in Ukraine reconnected with Rome — a story that's still shaping the Church today.</p>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/prayer-for-the-dead/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Theology</div>
        <h3>Why Do Catholics Pray for the Dead?</h3>
        <p>Because the Church is not a club for the living — it is the whole Body of Christ, across every border, including death.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 13</span></div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/library/filioque/`} class="library-card">
        <div class="library-card-cat">Theology</div>
        <h3>The Filioque Controversy</h3>
        <p>One word added to the Creed — "and the Son" — and a thousand-year conversation about what it means.</p>
        <div class="library-card-footer"><span class="tag">Journey Step 14</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .library-filter-bar {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .filter-chip {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--gold-10);
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    background: transparent;
  }
  .filter-chip:hover, .filter-chip.active {
    color: var(--halo-gold);
    border-color: var(--gold-40);
    background: var(--gold-06);
  }
  .library-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
  }
  .library-card {
    display: block;
    background: var(--icon-wall);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--gold-10);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 24px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, transform 0.2s;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }
  .library-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--gold-15);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
  .library-card-cat {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--halo-gold);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .library-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 19px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--beeswax);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .library-card p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--censer-smoke);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .library-card-footer {
    margin-top: 16px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .library-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
